# Plugin secrets and runtime state. docs/SETUP.md walks contributors through
# symlinking this repo into an Obsidian vault as the live plugin folder; once
# linked, Obsidian writes data.json next to the source. Without this rule a
# `git add .` ships real API keys (pre-1.0 builds; 1.0+ moves secrets to
# ~/.feynman/secrets.json, but data.json may still hold non-secret state
# the user doesn't want to commit).
data.json
.env
.env.*
.obsidian/
.feynman/

# Editor / IDE
.vscode/
.idea/

# Misc temp / backup
*.bak
*.tmp
